31
00:02:57,990 --> 00:02:58,710
Your food will be ready soon.

32
00:03:01,070 --> 00:03:01,660
Have some water.

33
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:12,990
Dr. Ruan.

34
00:03:13,190 --> 00:03:13,820
I heard

35
00:03:13,820 --> 00:03:15,550
you're working at Beiya Hospital.

36
00:03:15,990 --> 00:03:16,710
No.

37
00:03:16,790 --> 00:03:18,070
I work at West District Hospital.

38
00:03:18,460 --> 00:03:20,190
I'm only transferred
to Beiya Hospital temporarily.

39
00:03:21,070 --> 00:03:21,710
I see.

40
00:03:22,100 --> 00:03:22,790
That's not so bad.

41
00:03:23,100 --> 00:03:23,510
Well,

42
00:03:23,510 --> 00:03:24,990
I have much respect for doctors.

43
00:03:25,990 --> 00:03:26,460
Really?

44
00:03:26,660 --> 00:03:27,380
Yes.

45
00:03:28,020 --> 00:03:29,510
I have the utmost respect
for teachers too.

46
00:03:29,660 --> 00:03:30,380
Is that so?

47
00:03:40,860 --> 00:03:42,460
What was your major?

48
00:03:42,860 --> 00:03:44,350
I majored in Biology.

49
00:03:45,940 --> 00:03:47,630
Medicine and Biology
are practically one family.

50
00:03:47,910 --> 00:03:48,790
Yes, they're one family.

51
00:03:49,820 --> 00:03:50,820
We'll have a lot of things in common

52
00:03:50,820 --> 00:03:52,150
to talk about in the future.

53
00:03:52,430 --> 00:03:53,740
Actually, I never imagined

54
00:03:53,740 --> 00:03:54,630
I could be a doctor.

55
00:03:54,790 --> 00:03:55,630
I know what you mean.

56
00:03:56,020 --> 00:03:56,790
I can tell you this.

57
00:03:56,860 --> 00:03:58,350
When I studied in the United States,

58
00:03:58,350 --> 00:03:59,510
I majored in Biology, right?

59
00:03:59,510 --> 00:04:00,740
Do you know the difference

60
00:04:00,740 --> 00:04:01,990
between Biology and Medicine?

61
00:04:02,070 --> 00:04:02,510
What?

62
00:04:02,510 --> 00:04:04,300
We studied cells and bacteria all day.

63
00:04:16,020 --> 00:04:16,860
Slow down.

64
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:24,180
(Ban Tian Yao)

65
00:04:25,350 --> 00:04:26,300
Dad, look!

66
00:04:26,300 --> 00:04:27,510
- That's Mom.
- Dr. Ruan, you see.

67
00:04:28,420 --> 00:04:29,510
When I was in the United States,

68
00:04:29,510 --> 00:04:31,230
there were many interesting things.

69
00:04:31,230 --> 00:04:31,790
Really?

70
00:04:31,950 --> 00:04:32,300
Yes.

71
00:04:32,300 --> 00:04:33,390
Don't say anything foolish later.

72
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:34,390
Don't call her "Mom",

73
00:04:34,390 --> 00:04:35,020
understand?

74
00:04:35,350 --> 00:04:36,230
But she's my mom.

75
00:04:36,230 --> 00:04:37,300
Why can't I call her that?

76
00:04:38,110 --> 00:04:38,790
Just do as I say.

77
00:04:39,420 --> 00:04:40,580
I'll tell you about it next time.

78
00:04:49,140 --> 00:04:49,830
Ning Xiang.

79
00:04:53,950 --> 00:04:55,070
Madam.

80
00:05:00,190 --> 00:05:01,510
What are you doing here?

81
00:05:01,510 --> 00:05:03,790
I come here to learn painting
every week.

82
00:05:05,140 --> 00:05:05,580
Dr. Ruan,

83
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:07,910
this is...

84
00:05:11,020 --> 00:05:12,020
He's

85
00:05:12,630 --> 00:05:13,860
my mentor at Beiya Hospital.

86
00:05:13,860 --> 00:05:14,670
Mr. Ning.

87
00:05:15,630 --> 00:05:16,350
Ah, Mr. Ning.

88
00:05:16,790 --> 00:05:17,860
Hello, Mr. Ning.

89
00:05:18,140 --> 00:05:18,740
Hello.

90
00:05:18,740 --> 00:05:19,790
I'm Ge Qing.

91
00:05:20,070 --> 00:05:21,790
The characters used
for kudzu root and the color green.

92
00:05:22,580 --> 00:05:24,740
I'm Dr. Ruan's friend.

93
00:05:25,070 --> 00:05:25,910
I'm pleased to meet you.

94
00:05:26,190 --> 00:05:27,110
What's the matter?

95
00:05:27,790 --> 00:05:30,510
Who's that mister in the glasses?

96
00:05:31,950 --> 00:05:32,670
Can I choose

97
00:05:32,670 --> 00:05:33,980
not to answer your question?

98
00:05:34,070 --> 00:05:36,510
Are you on a date with him?

99
00:05:37,390 --> 00:05:39,350
Kid, you know quite a lot.

100
00:05:39,460 --> 00:05:40,300
Mr. Ning,

101
00:05:40,830 --> 00:05:42,300
it's such a coincidence.
I'm a teacher too.

102
00:05:42,790 --> 00:05:44,700
But I teach at a university.

103
00:05:46,830 --> 00:05:47,790
Oh? Which university?

104
00:05:47,910 --> 00:05:49,230
Nanhu University.

105
00:05:49,670 --> 00:05:51,390
I started working at the university

106
00:05:51,390 --> 00:05:52,540
after I returned from the United States.

107
00:05:52,670 --> 00:05:53,740
Some say

108
00:05:54,110 --> 00:05:55,350
teaching isn't a promising profession.

109
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:56,540
But

110
00:05:56,830 --> 00:05:57,790
I don't like a life competing
with others.

111
00:05:57,790 --> 00:05:59,420
- You don't look handsome if you're mad.
- I prefer

112
00:05:59,950 --> 00:06:00,950
a stable life.

113
00:06:01,460 --> 00:06:02,300
You also teach

114
00:06:02,580 --> 00:06:03,420
at a university, right?

115
00:06:05,070 --> 00:06:05,980
You can say that.

116
00:06:07,420 --> 00:06:08,390
Oh, come on. Don't be mad.

117
00:06:08,390 --> 00:06:09,390
By the way,

118
00:06:09,420 --> 00:06:11,390
does Zheng do well at the hospital?

119
00:06:13,580 --> 00:06:14,460
Zheng?

120
00:06:15,510 --> 00:06:16,300
I mean, Dr. Ruan.

121
00:06:18,910 --> 00:06:19,670
Zheng

122
00:06:19,830 --> 00:06:20,510
is doing pretty well.

123
00:06:21,110 --> 00:06:21,830
That's for sure.

124
00:06:22,110 --> 00:06:23,740
She's the most beautiful, intelligent,

125
00:06:24,020 --> 00:06:25,110
and lovely girl I've seen

126
00:06:25,110 --> 00:06:25,980
since I came back

127
00:06:25,980 --> 00:06:26,980
from the United States.

128
00:06:30,830 --> 00:06:31,790
We felt like seeing old friends
when we first met.

129
00:06:32,950 --> 00:06:33,950
She's my girlfriend.

130
00:06:36,420 --> 00:06:37,260
Girlfriend?

131
00:06:37,790 --> 00:06:38,630
Yes, girlfriend.

132
00:06:41,260 --> 00:06:41,860
It was only last week

133
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:42,790
she told us she was single.

134
00:06:44,350 --> 00:06:45,830
We just started dating.

135
00:06:45,830 --> 00:06:46,830
It hasn't been that long.

136
00:06:47,350 --> 00:06:48,860
Perhaps she hasn't told anyone yet.

137
00:06:54,020 --> 00:06:54,860
Mr. Ning,

138
00:06:55,670 --> 00:06:56,790
I heard it's difficult

139
00:06:56,790 --> 00:06:58,300
to get promoted in Beiya,

140
00:06:58,300 --> 00:06:58,860
right?

141
00:07:00,110 --> 00:07:01,110
I'm guessing

142
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:02,420
you're not over 35, right?

143
00:07:02,910 --> 00:07:03,580
I'm 34.

144
00:07:03,630 --> 00:07:04,950
You see, it's not easy

145
00:07:04,950 --> 00:07:05,670
to be an attending doctor

146
00:07:05,670 --> 00:07:06,510
at 34.

147
00:07:07,230 --> 00:07:08,350
Because your hospital

148
00:07:08,350 --> 00:07:09,740
is not like my university, right?

149
00:07:10,070 --> 00:07:11,350
Mine makes a lot of exceptions.

150
00:07:11,540 --> 00:07:12,110
You see,

151
00:07:12,350 --> 00:07:13,630
we're almost the same age.

152
00:07:14,460 --> 00:07:15,300
But I'm already

153
00:07:15,790 --> 00:07:16,510
the Associate Professor.

154
00:07:17,110 --> 00:07:18,140
It may be hard

155
00:07:18,670 --> 00:07:20,110
to get promoted.

156
00:07:20,110 --> 00:07:21,910
But I've at least made it,

157
00:07:22,190 --> 00:07:22,980
right?

158
00:07:23,460 --> 00:07:24,580
I need to take my son to class now.

159
00:07:24,580 --> 00:07:25,190
We're going to be late.

160
00:07:25,350 --> 00:07:26,070
I have to go now.

161
00:07:26,510 --> 00:07:27,350
Don't leave just yet.

162
00:07:27,980 --> 00:07:28,740
Since we ran into each other,

163
00:07:29,020 --> 00:07:29,950
why don't we have
a meal together someday?

164
00:07:31,140 --> 00:07:32,740
Zheng and I will be buying

165
00:07:33,230 --> 00:07:34,260
as thanks for taking good care of her.

166
00:07:36,190 --> 00:07:37,630
Bring your wife too.

167
00:07:39,230 --> 00:07:40,190
Wife?

168
00:07:40,390 --> 00:07:40,910
Yes,

169
00:07:41,670 --> 00:07:42,540
your wife.

170
00:07:42,830 --> 00:07:43,740
The wife of her mentor.

171
00:07:48,190 --> 00:07:48,950
Sure.

172
00:07:49,230 --> 00:07:49,950
No problem.

173
00:07:49,950 --> 00:07:50,540
It's a deal then.

174
00:07:51,070 --> 00:07:51,700
It's set then.

175
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:52,540
Ning Xiang,

176
00:07:54,860 --> 00:07:55,980
say goodbye to them.

177
00:07:56,260 --> 00:07:57,630
Goodbye.

178
00:07:57,910 --> 00:07:58,670
See you around.

179
00:07:58,670 --> 00:07:59,460
He's such a good boy.

180
00:07:59,740 --> 00:08:01,540
Dad, it's not this way.

181
00:08:01,540 --> 00:08:02,700
It's that way.

182
00:08:07,950 --> 00:08:08,860
Oh, Zheng.

183
00:08:08,980 --> 00:08:10,420
I promised to have a meal
with Mr. Kudzu Root here.

184
00:08:10,670 --> 00:08:12,300
I'll bring my wife

185
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:13,390
along for it.

186
00:08:14,460 --> 00:08:15,230
It's Ge Qing,

187
00:08:15,230 --> 00:08:16,230
from the color green.

188
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:17,140
Keep that in mind.

189
00:08:19,860 --> 00:08:21,110
He can't even remember my name.

190
00:08:22,140 --> 00:08:22,630
Let's go.

191
00:08:23,540 --> 00:08:24,350
Stop looking at them.

192
00:08:25,830 --> 00:08:27,420
You didn't talk much

193
00:08:27,420 --> 00:08:28,700
to Mr. Ning.

194
00:08:28,910 --> 00:08:29,860
It looks like

195
00:08:29,860 --> 00:08:30,910
you're closer to his son.

196
00:08:31,740 --> 00:08:33,270
Children like me.

197
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:35,900
By the way,

198
00:08:36,030 --> 00:08:37,950
how long will you stay at Beiya?

199
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:40,660
One year.

200
00:08:40,710 --> 00:08:42,100
Three months had passed.

201
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:43,710
I see.

202
00:08:44,630 --> 00:08:45,660
Why don't you transfer

203
00:08:46,100 --> 00:08:47,780
to a different hospital
for the next six months?

204
00:08:48,220 --> 00:08:49,100
That hospital

205
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:50,470
may be slightly worse than Beiya.

206
00:08:51,070 --> 00:08:52,470
But I know an Associate Professor

207
00:08:52,470 --> 00:08:53,220
in that hospital.

208
00:08:53,590 --> 00:08:54,950
It's better than you learning

209
00:08:54,950 --> 00:08:55,950
from this attending doctor.

210
00:08:57,510 --> 00:08:59,190
Did you say he's an attending doctor?

211
00:08:59,900 --> 00:09:01,220
Isn't he?

212
00:09:02,830 --> 00:09:03,900
He is a professor

213
00:09:03,950 --> 00:09:05,190
and the Deputy Manager.

214
00:09:06,420 --> 00:09:07,420
That's not possible.

215
00:09:08,030 --> 00:09:08,710
Isn't

216
00:09:08,710 --> 00:09:09,860
the Deputy Manager

217
00:09:09,860 --> 00:09:11,030
of Beiya to be at least 40 years old?

218
00:09:21,710 --> 00:09:22,950
The teacher told me

219
00:09:23,340 --> 00:09:24,470
you weren't paying attention

220
00:09:24,860 --> 00:09:26,030
in class today.

221
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:27,190
Is something troubling you?

222
00:09:31,630 --> 00:09:33,150
You can stop going to school
if you don't want to.

223
00:09:34,070 --> 00:09:35,630
No, I want to go to school.

224
00:09:35,900 --> 00:09:36,780
Then tell me

225
00:09:36,980 --> 00:09:38,070
what was on your mind today.

226
00:09:38,630 --> 00:09:40,630
My head hurt.

227
00:09:44,220 --> 00:09:44,980
Your head hurt?

228
00:09:46,780 --> 00:09:48,270
Not only my head hurt,

229
00:09:48,710 --> 00:09:50,830
but I also felt nauseated.

230
00:09:51,420 --> 00:09:52,390
You felt nauseated too?

231
00:09:53,950 --> 00:09:54,740
We must go to the hospital now.

232
00:09:57,390 --> 00:09:58,590
Some guy

233
00:09:58,590 --> 00:10:01,710
is going to steal my mom.

234
00:10:02,030 --> 00:10:04,030
What's the point
of going to the hospital?

235
00:10:04,220 --> 00:10:06,220
Doesn't your head hurt about this,

236
00:10:06,220 --> 00:10:07,150
Dad?

237
00:10:09,070 --> 00:10:09,780
What?

238
00:10:10,540 --> 00:10:13,190
That mister is worse than you.

239
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:15,900
I wanted to puke when I saw him.

240
00:10:16,590 --> 00:10:17,900
You little brat.

241
00:10:18,980 --> 00:10:19,540
So tell me.

242
00:10:19,540 --> 00:10:20,710
How is that mister worse than me?

243
00:10:20,860 --> 00:10:22,900
It's a child's instinct.

244
00:10:22,900 --> 00:10:24,630
A child's instinct?

245
00:10:24,740 --> 00:10:25,860
What a showoff.

246
00:10:26,100 --> 00:10:26,900
Be serious.

247
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:28,630
Dad,

248
00:10:28,830 --> 00:10:30,300
why don't you

249
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:32,070
just win my mom back?

250
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:34,780
Then you have a wife,

251
00:10:34,950 --> 00:10:35,980
and I'll have a mom.

252
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:37,710
It's indeed

253
00:10:37,860 --> 00:10:40,100
reaping two benefits in one action.

254
00:10:40,470 --> 00:10:42,780
Hitting two targets with an arrow.

255
00:10:43,340 --> 00:10:45,710
Killing two birds with one stone!

256
00:10:45,900 --> 00:10:47,950
You sure learned a lot of idioms lately.

257
00:10:48,270 --> 00:10:50,900
Think about what I said.

258
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:17,340
I'm home.

259
00:11:18,070 --> 00:11:18,740
You're home.

260
00:11:19,190 --> 00:11:19,860
Sufen,

261
00:11:19,950 --> 00:11:21,190
hurry. Liuzheng is home.

262
00:11:21,340 --> 00:11:21,900
Come on.

263
00:11:24,150 --> 00:11:25,340
You're home?

264
00:11:26,420 --> 00:11:27,190
What do you think?

265
00:11:27,630 --> 00:11:28,340
What do you mean?

266
00:11:28,710 --> 00:11:30,300
The guy, your aunt introduced you to.

267
00:11:33,100 --> 00:11:33,900
He's neither that good nor bad.

268
00:11:34,340 --> 00:11:35,390
Is he tall?

269
00:11:36,030 --> 00:11:36,710
He's neither tall nor short.

270
00:11:37,190 --> 00:11:37,830
Then...

271
00:11:37,980 --> 00:11:39,030
He's neither fat nor thin.

272
00:11:40,660 --> 00:11:42,340
Do you two get along?

273
00:11:42,780 --> 00:11:43,900
Do you have anything
in common to talk about?

274
00:11:44,660 --> 00:11:46,300
What is his job title?

275
00:11:46,470 --> 00:11:47,780
What do his parents do for a living?

276
00:11:48,420 --> 00:11:48,740
Mom,

277
00:11:49,220 --> 00:11:50,590
it's my first time meeting him.

278
00:11:50,740 --> 00:11:51,510
If I asked him all these,

279
00:11:51,740 --> 00:11:52,740
it would feel like I'm probing into
his family matters.

280
00:11:55,100 --> 00:11:56,710
Don't tell me you told him by mistake.

281
00:11:57,590 --> 00:11:58,300
What?

282
00:11:59,300 --> 00:12:01,030
About you and Zhiqian's divorce.

283
00:12:01,740 --> 00:12:02,660
What do you mean?

284
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:03,900
Didn't Aunt tell him about it?

285
00:12:07,220 --> 00:12:08,070
We planned

286
00:12:08,070 --> 00:12:10,420
to wait until you've secured
his feelings.

287
00:12:10,420 --> 00:12:11,150
Then

288
00:12:11,420 --> 00:12:12,190
perhaps

289
00:12:12,190 --> 00:12:13,540
he wouldn't mind about it.

290
00:12:13,740 --> 00:12:15,340
Do you think we can hide it from him?

291
00:12:16,150 --> 00:12:17,150
We can't do this to him.

292
00:12:18,220 --> 00:12:19,030
That's right.

